<section class="card">
  <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

  <details>
    <summary>What if I don’t know my last frost date?</summary>
    <p>
      Start by looking up your average last frost date, then use that as your anchor.
      See: <a href="/guides/how-to-find-your-last-frost-date/">how to find your last frost date</a>.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Can I plant before my last frost date?</summary>
    <p>
      Sometimes, depending on the crop and protection. Cold-tolerant crops can handle light frost, but warm-season crops can’t.
      Treat last frost as a planning anchor, then adjust with real conditions.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>What if I miss my indoor start window?</summary>
    <p>
      You can buy starts, direct sow faster crops, or choose shorter-season varieties.
      Missing a week is rarely a problem — missing a month changes the plan.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Should I start seeds earlier in colder climates?</summary>
    <p>
      Usually no. Starting earlier doesn’t automatically extend your outdoor season.
      Focus on transplant timing, variety choice, and protection where it actually helps.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

